article.description: Kentrell Barkley scored 13 points, collected 10 rebounds and his 3-point play with one second left lifted East Carolina to a 64-61 win over Temple Wednesday night.
article.headline: Barkley propels East Carolina past Temple 64-61
article.linkText: Barkley propels East Carolina past Temple 64-61
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. -- Kentrell Barkley scored 13 points, collected 10 rebounds and his 3-point play with one second left lifted East Carolina to a 64-61 win over Temple Wednesday night. Barkley gathered an offensive rebound off Prince Williams' miss with five seconds left before burying the game winner. Williams -- who finished with 18 points -- scored seven straight points for the Pirates before the miss. Temple's Josh Brown made two free throws with 21 seconds left to tie it at 61. Obi Enechionyia hit a 3 with 9:31 left to play to give Temple at 52-47 lead, the largest lead either team held in the contest. Enechionyia led the Owls with 18 points. East Carolina (10-11, 2-6 American Athletic) got 14 points from B.J. Tyson. Williams and Tyson made 12 of Temple's 25 field goals. Quenton DeCosey had 14 points and 11 boards for Temple (11-8, 5-3).
